Package io.j4c.config.spi

Interface OverrideSource

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Changeable<OverrideSource.OverrideData>, Source<OverrideSource.OverrideData>, Supplier<OverrideSource>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractOverrideSource

    public interface OverrideSource
extends Source<OverrideSource.OverrideData>, Supplier<OverrideSource>
    OverrideSource SPI allows overriding of existing values.

    Override source provides a list of pairs of Predicate<Config.Key> and String value. The configuration keys are evaluated on predicates in the given order until the key matches the first predicate. Then the original value is replaced by the one given by the predicate.

    The document format is Java Properties. The key token may contain a valid string as is specified in Config.Key or * for any value.

    Override definitions are applied before any filter.

    Note that overridden can be only those entries, which are already defined in any config source. It means that no additional configuration entry won't be created by overrides.
